The Labour Court has dismissed an urgent application to stop SAA retrenchments. Unions Numsa and the SA Cabin Crew Association filed the application. SAA's business rescue practitioners decided to cut several routes to save money. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Trade unions have warned they will fight to the bitter end to prevent retrenchments at SAA. This after the Labour Court dismissed an urgent application by Numsa and the SA Cabin Crew Association to stop retrenchments at SAA. READ: Liquidation of SAA, SA Express not off the table The unions now say they will appeal the court's decision. “We must appeal this decision. 10,000 families will be affected by this decision. This is a battle for survival and we would do anything absolutely possible to save workers jobs,” said Numsa spokesperson Phakamile Hlubi-Majola. WATCH: Court dismisses interdict by unions in SAA retrenchments SAA says while lay-offs are inevitable, the company has not flouted any labour laws. The airline says it will ensure that all obligations to staff are met.